author: Russell Brand
description:
Go to https://TryFum.com/RUSSELLBRAND or scan the QR code and use code RUSSELLBRAND to get your free FÜM Topper when you order your Journey Pack today!

George Galloway — a five-time MP, a voice of defiance against the establishment — arrested under the Terrorism Act at Gatwick. What does it say when outspoken figures are treated as threats for their words, not their actions? From Linehan to Bridgen to Galloway, the message is clear: dissent is criminalized, liberty is fading, and Britain’s democracy is rotting from within. If even the rebels of Parliament can be silenced, what chance do the rest of us have unless we demand new systems of power rooted in truth and accountability?
